 Here is a simple JavaScript program that generates the ASCII character and its corresponding hexadecimal code for each value from 0 to 7F:

```javascript
for(let i = 0; i <= 7F; i++) {
    console.log(`Character: ${String.fromCharCode(i)}, Hex Code: ${i.toString(16)}`);
}
```

This script uses `String.fromCharCode()` method to convert the Unicode code point (in this case, a number from 0 to 7F) into a string containing one or more characters, and then logs it along with its hexadecimal representation using `toString(16)`.
